-- Ontario Teachers in Talks With Goals Soccer, Sky News Reports
-- B y   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 2012-03-31T11:39:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-31/ontario-teachers-in-talks-with-goals-soccer-sky-news-reports.html
Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan ,
Canada’s third-largest pension fund, is in talks with  Goals
Soccer Centres Plc (GOAL)  to take the company private, Sky News
reported, without citing sources. The talks are at an early
stage, Sky reported on its  website .  Goals Soccer has a market value of 52.3 million pounds 
(US$84 million) based on its closing share price in London 
yesterday of 107.5 pence.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Nandini Sukumar in London at 
 nsukumar@bloomberg.net  or @NandiniSukumar on Twitter  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
